# Database Migration Safety

Apply this rule when editing schema definitions or data-shape assumptions.

## Required Updates

If either file changes:

- `server/db/schema.ts`
- `database/schema.sql`

Then also update:

- `database/migrations/*.sql`
- `database/migrations/meta/*` (when generated/required)

## Consistency Rules

- Keep Drizzle schema and SQL schema in parity.
- Prefer additive, non-destructive migration paths for hosted environments.
- Document operational impact in changelog/docs when schema behavior changes.

## Verification

- Run migration/type/test checks before commit for schema-related work.
